        108.与人同行是成为伟人的捷径<br/>
        The path to greatness is along with others<br/>
        109.不要吹毛求疵<br/>
        Be not censorious<br/>
        110.不要坐以待毙<br/>
        Do not wait till you are a sinking sun<br/>
        111.赢得朋友<br/>
        Have friends<br/>
        112.博取他人的好感<br/>
        Gain good-will<br/>
        113.未雨绸缪<br/>
        In prosperity prepare for adversity<br/>
        114.避免与人相争<br/>
        Never compete<br/>
        115.习惯熟人的缺点<br/>
        Get used to the failings of your familiars<br/>
        116.只和可敬之人交往<br/>
        Only act with honourable men<br/>
        117.决不谈论自己<br/>
        Never talk about yourself<br/>
        118.要赢得谦恭有礼的名声<br/>
        Acquire the reputation of courtesy<br/>
        119.避免惹人厌烦<br/>
        Avoid becoming disliked<br/>
        120.生活讲求实际<br/>
        Live practically<br/>
        121.不要小题大做<br/>
        Do not make a business of what is no business<br/>
        122.言行应有威信<br/>
        Distinction in speech and action<br/>
        123.避免矫揉造作<br/>
        Avoid affectation<br/>
        124.要被他人想念<br/>
        Get yourself missed<br/>
        125.不要成为污点记录簿<br/>
        Do not be a black list<br/>
        126.愚蠢并非做了蠢事，而在于做后不知掩饰<br/>
        Folly consists not in<br/>
        committing folly, but in not hiding it when committed<br/>
        127.凡是从容优雅<br/>
        Grace in everything<br/>
        128.要有高远的志向<br/>
        Highmindedness<br/>
        129.从不抱怨<br/>
        Never complain<br/>
        130.要干，且要让人看见<br/>
        Do and be seen doing<br/>
        131.慷慨大度<br/>
        Nobility of feeling<br/>
        132.修正自己的判断<br/>
        Revise your judgments<br/>
        133.宁可同醉，而不独醒<br/>
        Better mad with the rest of the world than wise alone<br/>
        134.加倍储存你的资源<br/>
        Double your resources<br/>
        135.不要滋长唱反调的习气<br/>
        Do not nourish the spirit of contradiction<br/>
        136.抓住事情关键<br/>
        Post yourself in the centre of things<br/>
        137.圣人自足<br/>
        The sage should be self-sufficing<br/>
        138.任其自然的艺术<br/>
        The art of letting things alone<br/>
        139.冷静面对倒霉的日子<br/>
        Recognize unlucky days<br/>
        140.一眼看到事物好的一面<br/>
        Find the good in a thing at once<br/>
        141.不要只倾听自己的声音<br/>
        Do not listen to yourself<br/>
        142.当对手先站在正确的一方时,你不能固执地站在错误的一方<br/>
        Never from obstinacy take the wrong side because your<br/>
        opponent has anticipated you in taking the right one<br/>
        143.别为免俗而玩弄诡辩之术<br/>
        Never become paradoxical in order to avoid the trite<br/>
        144.开始于他人，受用于自己<br/>
        Begin with another&#39;s to end with your own<br/>
        145.藏好你受伤的手指<br/>
        Do not show your wounded finger<br/>
        146.透过现象看本质<br/>
        Look into the interior of things<br/>
        147.采纳他人的建议<br/>
        Do not be inaccessible<br/>
        148.掌握谈话的艺术<br/>
        Have the art of conversation<br/>
        149.懂得推罪于人<br/>
        Know how to put off ills on others<br/>
        150.推销得法<br/>
        Know how to get your price for things<br/>
        151.高瞻远瞩<br/>
        Think beforehand<br/>
        152.不与令自己黯然失色之人为伍<br/>
        Never have a companion who casts you in the shade<br/>
        153.不要去填补前人留下的巨大空缺<br/>
        Beware of entering where there is a great gap to be filled<br/>
        154.不轻易相信，也不轻易喜欢<br/>
        Do not believe, or like, lightly<br/>
        155.掌控激情的艺术<br/>
        The art of mastering your passions<br/>
        156.选择你的朋友<br/>
        Select your friends<br/>
        157.识人别出错<br/>
        Do not make mistakes about character<br/>
        158.善用朋友<br/>
        Make use of your friends<br/>
        159.忍受愚蠢<br/>
        Put up with fools<br/>
        160.说话要谨慎<br/>
        Be careful in speaking<br/>
        161.认清自身喜爱的缺点<br/>
        Know your pet faults<br/>
        162.如何战胜对手和诽谤者<br/>
        How to triumph over rivals and detractors<br/>
        163.决不因同情而卷入他人的不幸<br/>
        Never, from sympathy with the unfortunate,<br/>
        involve yourself in his fate<br/>
        164.投石问路<br/>
        Throw straws in the air<br/>
        165.斗争也要讲体面<br/>
        Wage war honourably<br/>
        166.分辨善言者与善行者<br/>
        Distinguish the man of words from the man of deeds<br/>
        167.知道怎样依靠自己<br/>
        Know how to take your own part<br/>
        168.不要沦为愚蠢的怪物<br/>
        Do not indulge in the eccentricities of folly<br/>
        169.多加小心，避免万一失手胜过百发百中<br/>
        Be more careful not to miss once<br/>
        than to hit a hundred times<br/>
        170.凡事有所保留<br/>
        In all things keep something in reserve<br/>
        171.不要滥用人情<br/>
        Do not waste influence<br/>
        172.决不与一无所有者争斗<br/>
        Never contend with a man who has nothing to lose<br/>
        173.与人相交，不要像玻璃般易碎，朋友间尤其如此<br/>
        Do not be glass in intercourse, still less in friendship<br/>
        174.不要活在匆忙中<br/>
        Do not live in a hurry<br/>
        175.做个实在的人<br/>
        A solid man<br/>
        176.自知或从知者处知<br/>
        Have knowledge, or know those that have knowledge<br/>
        177.避免与人太亲近<br/>
        Avoid familiarities in intercourse<br/>
        178.信赖你的内心<br/>
        Trust your heart<br/>
        179.缄默是才能的标志<br/>
        Reticence is the seal of capacity<br/>
        180.决不被敌人误导<br/>
        Never be guided by what your enemy has done<br/>
        ……<br/>
        295.若未奏效，不要邀功<br/>
        Do not affect what you have not effected<br/>
        296.高贵的品质<br/>
        Noble qualities<br/>
        297.行动总如处于监视中<br/>
        Always act as if your acts were seen<br/>
        298.可造就非凡之人的三大要素<br/>
        Three things go to a prodigy<br/>
        299.让人有饥饿感<br/>
        Leave off hungry<br/>
        300.总而言之，做一位圣徒<br/>
        In one word, be a saint<br/>
     · · · · · ·     (<a href="javascript:$('#dir_3260902_full').hide();$('#dir_3260902_short').show();void(0);">收起</a>)
</div>



  















  






